{{expert needed|1=Mythology|date=August 2017|reason=The tone is perhaps not suited to an encyclopaedic article, and I question the use of the info box which suggests an inappropriate level of accurcay.}} ''For the Kingdom of Fib see [[Kingdom of Fib]].''
{{Infobox royalty|name=Fib/Fibaid|succession=[[List of kings of Fib|King of Fib]]|reign=715-691 BCE {{Citation needed|date=August 2017}}|predecessor=Founder of Fib|successor=[[Gede-olgudach]] (possibly)|birth_date=After 822 BCE|death_date=7th Century BCE (age c. 161)|father=[[King Cruithne|Cruithne]]|succession1=Pictish Ruler|successor1=[[Gede-olgudach]]|predecessor1=[[Fortriu / Fortrann / Fortrenn]]}}
'''Fib''' is a mythological Pictish prince mentioned in the [[Pictish Chronicle]]. He was king of the Fib Kingdom (Fife), he ruled for 24 years along with his brothers, Cat, Fidach, Cé, Fótla, Circinn and Fortriu. He was the son of Cruithne, king of all of the Picts who supposedly ruled for 100 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.historyfiles.co.uk/KingListsBritain/GaelsPictland.htm|title=Kingdoms of Caledonia & Ireland - Pictland|last=Kessler|first=P L|website=www.historyfiles.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> Fib's rule may of been 715-691 BCE according to the Pictish Chronicles "Fibaid xxiiij" which translates to Fib ruled for 24 years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kjhskj75z.talktalk.net/pictish.html|title=THE PICTISH CHRONICLE|website=www.kjhskj75z.talktalk.net|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref>{{unreliable source?|date=July 2017}} The chronicles also state that the brothers ruled one after the other.<gallery> File:FifeTraditional.png|Map of the Kingdom of Fib (Traditional Fife) File:Pictish kingdoms with Fidach.png|Pictish kingdoms </gallery>
